President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation ordering that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff in memory of Shimon Peres, the former President and Prime Minister of Israel. The flag will be flown at half-staff at the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on September 30, 2016. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.